# Patterns (regex) for links lychee should not check.
# The config $schema URL is an identifier, not a resolvable page (yet).
https://dcyfr\.ai/schema/config\.json
# 1Password references in .env.example are not URLs.
^op://
# Local/dev endpoints used as config examples.
localhost
127\.0\.0\.1
example\.com
# Valid links that 403 automated checkers via bot protection (fine in a browser).
npmjs\.com
platform\.openai\.com
# 3rd-party doc host that intermittently 500s (transient server errors that
# survive --max-retries 3 and would flake this hard gate). The page is valid;
# we don't control its uptime.
docs\.msty\.studio
# release-please-generated CHANGELOG compare links. The newest entry's
# vN-1...vN URL 404s until the release tag is pushed (the release PR merges
# before tagging), so every PR opened in that window reds this hard gate --
# currently v3.4.2...v3.4.3 (tag v3.4.3 not yet pushed). The URLs are
# machine-generated and become valid at tag time; a 404 here never indicates
# a doc error a PR author can fix.
https://github\.com/dcyfr-labs/dcyfr-ai/compare/
